do you have to use an external drive or cd?

You can partition your hard drive into two, using the Disk Utility in the Utilities folder in the Application folder. In the Help section, learn to create a 2nd 12 GB partition, without deleting the old of course. Then use "Restore" to this disk image as the source and the new partition as the destination. Restart booting from the new partition and install Snow Leopard. That's what I did. Worked fine. No need to buy an external drive or blank DL DVD.
